-- McDonald’s to Expand in Baltic Growth Region, Verslo Zinios Says
-- B y   B r y a n   B r a d l e y
-- 2012-11-22T08:27:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-22/mcdonald-s-to-expand-in-baltic-growth-region-verslo-zinios-says.html
McDonald’s Corp. (MCD)  is expanding its
fast-food chain in Lithuania, Latvia and  Estonia , whose
economies are growing at the fastest pace in the European Union,
Verslo Zinios reported.  The company plans to invest 23 million euros ($29.5
million) by 2015 to open new restaurants in the three Baltic
nations, the Vilnius, Lithuania-based  newspaper said, citing
Tomasz Nawrocki, Baltic managing director for Premier Capital
Ltd., which represents McDonald’s in the region and holds
franchise rights.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Bryan Bradley in Vilnius at 
 bbradley13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Balazs Penz at 
 bpenz@bloomberg.net  